主要翻译
 
wade ▦ vi (walk through water)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 涉水 shè shuǐ  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 蹚水 shè shuǐ，tāng shuǐ 
 -- Her mother told her not to wade out too far in case the tide dragged her under.
 -- 她妈妈告诫她别涉水太深，以免被潮汐卷走。

动词短语 
 
wade in vi phrasal figurative (intervene)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 介入, 干涉  
 
wade in vi phrasal figurative, informal (weigh in: offer opinion)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 插话, 介入  (在辩论时)
 -- At the meeting, Freya's boss told her to wade in if she had any better ideas.
 
wade in on [sth] vi phrasal + prep figurative, informal (weigh in on: offer an opinion about)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 在...问题上提出自己的看法  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 就...发表己见 
 -- Charlie couldn't resist wading in on the discussion, even though he had no expertise in the subject.
 
wade in with [sth] vi phrasal + prep figurative, informal (weigh in with: offer opinion, support)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 对...发表自己的看法  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 对...表示支持 

复合形式： 
 
wade in vi + adv (walk into water, mud, etc.)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 蹚, 涉过, 跋涉  
 -- There was no bridge over the creek, so to cross it I had to wade in.
 
wade into [sth] vi + prep (walk into: deep water or mud)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 抨击，攻击 pēng jī，gōng jī TC Traditional Chinese 抨擊，攻擊  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 猛烈袭击，强行介入 měng liè xí jī，qiáng xíng jiè rù 
 -- Joe waded into the water to see how deep it was.
 
wade into [sth] vi + prep figurative (enter: an argument)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 强行介入 qiáng xíng jiè rù  (辩论、争执等)
 -- Don't wade into their arguments about money.
 
wade into [sth] vi + prep figurative (intervene)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 抨击，攻击 pēng jī，gōng jī TC Traditional Chinese 抨擊，攻擊  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 猛烈袭击，强行介入 měng liè xí jī，qiáng xíng jiè rù 
 -- Both the Prime Minister and the Leader of the Opposition have waded into the situation by commenting on the scandal.
 
wade through [sth] vi + prep (walk through: deep water or mud)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 吃力地做完 chī lì de zuò wán  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 费劲地处理 chī lì de zuò wán，fèi jìn de chǔ lǐ 
 -- It rained so much I had to wade through water to get to my house.
 
wade through [sth] vi + prep figurative (work through: tedious)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 吃力地做完 chī lì de zuò wán  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 费劲地处理完 
 -- I'm too tired to wade through all this work tonight. I'll do it tomorrow.
 -- 我太累了，今天晚上是处理不完这些工作了，明天再说吧。

